---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Harvey Brooks — Editor | CreditDoc"
  description="Harvey Brooks is the editor overseeing hand-reviewed lender profiles on CreditDoc."
  canonical="https://www.creditdoc.co/about/harvey-brooks/"
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-muted mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a> <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <a href="/about/" class="hover:text-primary">About</a> <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span>Harvey Brooks</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Harvey Brooks</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-muted mb-8">Editor, CreditDoc</p>

    <section class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Role</h2>
      <p>
        Harvey Brooks serves as editor for CreditDoc's hand-reviewed lender
        profiles. He is responsible for verifying that the written content
        on a small set of flagship profiles accurately represents each
        lender's products, pricing, and customer experience.
      </p>

      <h2>Scope of Editorial Review</h2>
      <p>
        Editorial review at CreditDoc is reserved for our flagship profile
        set. As of today, roughly 200 of the 20,000+ lender pages on
        CreditDoc carry editorial review. The rest are automatically
        compiled from public regulatory filings (NCUA, FDIC, HUD) and
        publicly available business information.
      </p>

      <h2>What Editorial Review Is</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Every fact in the written review is verified against the lender's own website or a primary-source regulator</li>
        <li>Products, pricing tiers, fees, and eligibility criteria are confirmed</li>
        <li>Pros and cons reflect real strengths and gaps, not generic boilerplate</li>
        <li>The profile is only published once the editor is satisfied it is accurate</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What Editorial Review Is Not</h2>
      <p>
        Editorial review does <strong>not</strong> set the star rating.
        All CreditDoc Ratings are derived from our 5-factor algorithmic
        methodology — see our <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a>
        for how scores are computed and what data sources feed each factor.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For editorial corrections or feedback, please use the contact form
        on our <a href="/about/">About page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
